parameters: Mage Relm: Cough cough... It's a dusty place, isn't it?

Priestess Sophia: The visibility is quite poor here. It
wouldn't be surprising if we were attacked.

Thief Nora: It's not just that. I can hear multiple sounds,
it seems like there are animals wandering around too.

Clea: We don't know where the enemies are. Everyone, proceed
with caution.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Priestess Sophia: It's quite dim, but is this the statue of
the goddess Delia...?

Priestess Sophia: Perhaps this place was a temple dedicated
to the goddess Delia.
Thief Nora: Should we pray in front of the statue after all?

Thief Nora: I was thinking that maybe it's better to pray in
front of the statue, where the priestess can hear us...

Thief Nora: I smell blood... in multiple places... different
ones.

Thief Nora: I'm moving by jumping! They're gradually getting
closer to us!
Thief Nora: Is this the sound of chains...?

Thief Nora: I've landed in front of the statue of the
goddess! Come over here!
Priestess Sophia: I'm going to heal now, kyaa!?

Thief Nora: I-It's okay, big sis, because you're also a
beastkin like me!

Thief Nora: I'll heal your injuries! So come over here...
Don't be scared, you can trust me, okay?

Mage Relm: The words Nora-san spoke before the first scream
sounded similar.
Mage Relm: I can't believe Delia's Dagger was a beastkin.
Thief Nora: Don't be scared, it's okay...

Thief Nora: Relm-san! Please make it so that you can
understand any language!

Thief Nora: This child is really frightened! If I don't do
something, me, me!

Mage Relm: It's impossible... The language of the beastkin
has not been deciphered even in the Academy.

Cors the Wanderer: So this child is Delia's Dagger? I never
imagined that the entire Mucos would be manipulated by a
child.
Thief Nora: Cors-san! Can you help save this child!?

Thief Nora: There must have been a reason for it. I did do
something bad, but it's okay, right!?
Cors the Wanderer: I'm relying on all of you, you know.

Thief Nora: I'm glad...! If we have time, we will definitely
be able to get along--

Cors the Wanderer: In the underworld, there's a thing called
'face' within organizations, you know.

Thief Nora: Captain! Please step aside! This child, my
fellow kin!

Cors the Wanderer: Our members were killed by this child and
also suffered significant losses from the suspicious rival
organization.

Cors the Wanderer: My subordinates... This was an
unnecessary conversation, wasn't it?

Cors the Wanderer: Please make sure to leave the corpses
there. I will come later with the young ones to collect
them.

Thief Nora: I'm sorry... I couldn't do anything... Ugh, I'm
sorry...

Thief Nora: Huh, the language... It's the language of the
Empire...! I can speak it, it's okay, I understand!
Dagger of Delay... Pain... Stop... Hate... Scared...
Thief Nora: I don't know, I don't know...!

Thief Nora: I should have known... but I don't understand
anything!

Thief Nora: Please don't stop me, I absolutely won't
forgive... I will avenge them.

Captain Clevo: If you still choose to go and kill Cors after
hearing my story, I won't stop you.

Captain Clevo: I don't know the background of that beastman
child, but there is no doubt that they continued to
indiscriminately kill in Mucos.

Captain Clevo: I'm not saying that everyone was a good
person, but there must have been some who were not involved.

Captain Clevo: What could we have done against a murderous
beastman child who doesn't understand words?

Captain Clevo: Are you going to put her in a cage and chain
her up? Nora, everything is different from your time.
Thief Nora: Even so, even so, I will!

Captain Clevo: Cors may be in the wrong, but I can't think
of any other way.
Thief Nora: I'm sorry! Uwaaaah, I'm sorry, uuuuuh, aaaaah!
